inn1.comm: Marshall turns Lee to midwicket and he's off the mark immediately
Gayle leaves outside off
full delivery again with a hint of swing away, driven out to mid on and that's a wayward throw from Pollard
on the front foot, driven straight through long off, lovely straight drive on the up
forced it right across him, the batsman shoulders arms and lets it go through
outside off, a thick edge is controlled down to third man and Australia will be pleased with their first over having been sent in
oh, good start! Some movement away and the batsman shoulders arms
pushed off the front foot in line with off and it's wristed into short midwicket
outside off, pushes it past the outside edge, the batsman presses forward on the front foot and it goes on through
outside off, played down into the gully area
poor delivery from Gayle gets the treatment, dragging it down on and outside leg and Watson isn't slow to pull hard round and through fine leg
down on one knee, pulled to square this time
forced across the left hander from over the wicket, some encouraging lift off the track as it angles awkwardly but the leave is well judged
hurried across him once more, a touch flatter this time
steps down the track and defends back down middle
on the legs, squeezed to short midwicket and they think about running but in comes the call "No!"
right past him this time, some good line and length there and just leaves the outside edge as the batsman gets on the back foot
some width outside off and driven hard through the covers - a touch of air in that drive which will encourage West Indies
on the legs, squeezed down to fine leg, somehow finding room
fired across him, some swing back in to the left hander who gets right over the ball in front-foot defence just outside off
outside off, the batsman shoulders arms this time
sends it wider to tempt him into a loose shot, instead Marsh gets hold of a cover drive
some swing back in, straight, but the batsman manages to press forward, a mere caress
bangs it in and Watson turns it well off his legs behind square
oh, squares right behind that one and the batsman's beaten as the ball pitches on middle and deviates off past the off stump
he gets bat on it this time, opening the face and running it down to third man
pushed off the front foot down to the gully
short ball outside off and pulled straight through mid on, a good shot, into it quickly and lifted into safety
outside off, the batsman runs it down to third man once again
wide down the leg side this time
some swing in on off, pushed forward gently and they charge through the quick single
some swing and width outside off, runs it down to third man
dragged it down a touch short and brushed into the leg side
brushed off the legs out to square and some excellent running to get back in, really making the most of the runs on offer
driven out very straight right through the stumps and it's just to say stopped inside the rope - the ball slowed up a touch by crashing on to the sticks at the non-striker's end
width outside off, some swing away and Watson is tempted into having a slay away from his body, the ball going from the base of the bat up and over point, squarer than he was aiming for
on the front foot, pushed down to gully
on the legs and eased off the hips down to fine leg
short and wide outside off, cut into the covers off the back foot
on the legs, and picked off quite easily to midwicket, the strike rotated once more
on middle and leg, played out to square and they come back for the easy two
outside off, the ball goes through on a good length and left alone
too wide outside off this time
outside off, the ball doesn't get up so much, Watson cuts it down into the track
starts over the wicket and puts the ball in line with off, a good length, defended forward
a touch straighter, and pushed to the on side now
some width outside off, pushed to short midwicket
drags it down a touch, but the loop is enough to make the batsman think of defending, pushing to the leg side

on the up now and the batsman pushes to mid on, there's a mix-up between Watson and Benn, the bowler falling over in follow-through and trapping Watson's bat under him. The batsman recovers, picks himself up and charges through the single
round the wicket now and makes Watson think about it, beating his outside edge
on the legs, pushed out straightish to mid on although the initial movement looked like he was going to tuck off his hips
down the legs and half an appeal from the keeper for a strangle down to the keeper, who took it in front of him
short ball, pushed out to point
wristed off the front foot out to square
another quick single
run down to third man off the back foot
outside off, turned back in from over the wicket and the batsman pushes forward on the front foot
goes for the sweep this time, the batsman coming outside off stump but it doesn't go to his plan
a fair push down the ground to long on and they come back for two
slower slow one this time, some wild movement back in from outside off forces the front-foot defence
more of the same
shuffles across his stumps once more and this time connects with the sweep only for his plans to be thwarted by the man at backward square leg
nipped back in from outside off, the batsman pushes to short point and they jog through
short ball, straight and Marsh just steps back and pulls hard well through square, pure power and timing
a better length, fuller, and played forward into the off side
on the legs, the batsman spots it early but hasn't quite picked the speed and as he looks to push it to the legs the ball pops up and goes forward

pushed across him, the batsman goes for the late cut and gets a thick edge over the vacant slip area, and Marshall runs in, slides and lands awkwardly on his right shoulder, returns with his left arm, can't point with his right hand, and his back foot appears to have only bridely connected with the rope, but it's enough
outside off, driven to the covers
the lap sweep from Watson who's quickly down the track outside off, exposes the stumps and connects well through fine leg
defended hard on the front foot
up there on off, round-armed in and the batsman defends on the front foot
drags it a touch short, doesn't get up much, and Watson has to use all hiw power and pull hard in front of midwicket
good reply, Watson this time forced to defend into the covers on the back foot
outside off, again not much lift, the batsman crouches down, opens the face and runs it through third man, the ball rolling along happily although it's not the fastest outfield
outside off, runs it down to third man
forced across him once more, a defence off the back foot back down the line
outside off, played into the covers
swivel-pulled round to midwicket

a huge shout as Watson walks right across his stumps - something he's been favouring this innings - and the ball comes in , pitching just outside off and rapping him in line with leg, Watson too late on the would-be flick off the legs
some width outside off and Ponting leaves it first up
width outside off and cut hard through backward point for four
comes down the track and drives out in front of midwicket
floated in on off and worked out in front of square, Ponting's not interested in the second, Marsh is and chaos ensues - albeit briefly - Marsh is halfway down the track and has to get right back in
on the front foot, defended forward, the bowler coming in round the wicket
defended forward
defended hard once again, to the gully now
comes in on the legs and brushed back out behind square
on the front foot, comes forward and closes the face on one which is in line with off, flicking it out to midwicket
some width outside off, drives hard through the covers to bring up his fifty on his one-day debut, the eighth Australian to make a half-century on ODI debut
a wide down the leg side, can't much argue with that one
overpitched outside off, driven hard to the man at mid off
slower ball, and a good one, comes in on the legs and pushed out on the leg side, the ball popping up but without too much danger
outside off, some width, cut behind gully
on the front foot, driven out to mid on
extra loop, Ponting waits and drives out to mid off
comes back in from outside off, pushed to the covers and they charge through, some good running there
gets on the back foot, waits and cuts into the covers
a bit of a false stroke I'm afraid this time, cutting hard at one which comes in wider and flatter. Good bowling
defended on the front foot outside off
outside off, stands on the back foot and guides it down to third man
on off, steps down and has to check the shot, almost a hockey-like controlled flick towards mid on along the ground
some swing away, driven out to mid off
overpitched on off, pushed back towards the bowler
pitched up there, the batsman forces out to mid off
on the legs, worked out forward without much power
ballooning ball comes on the legs, and it's swept round easily through backward square
drives hard to the covers for a single
over the wicket again, comes out and defends forward
on the knee and swept round through the 45
back round the wicket, defended on the front foot into the covers
width outside off, Ponting doesn't quite get hold of a work to the covers
angled in to pitch in line with off, and Marsh is quick to jump into the line and defend on the front foot
outside off, the ball sits up and asks to be cut out off the back foot through point. The batsman obliges
some width right outside off and Ponting looks to slam it to the covers but instead drags a thick inside edge a long way and back onto the sticks
lets this one go through, the batsman shouldering arms now
Clarke pushes into the covers this time, waiting for the ball to angle across him
hustles across him, the batsman shouldering arms. Neat over from the bowler, including a handy wicket
steps across outside off, looking to sweep it to the legs, does so, and they scramble the single. Then comes the danger - Marsh halfway down the track and has to get back quickly as the ball comes in
back round the wicket, super delivery, drawing Clarke forward and curving away from his outside edge
on the front foot, the batsman pushes out towards the covers
some big loop, the batsman pushes on the front foot, once more unto the covers
some width outside off, some calls of "Wait on" and "Catch it, catch it" as the ball's cut down to the gully
again both calls, this time the batsman pushes to the covers
comes in straight and the batsman is nearly cut in half as he bends over what would be a pull
back over the wicket for the right hander, who presses defensively on the front foot towards the covers
up there on the legs, defended right forward
some big width outside off, cut to point
Clarke gets a run now, looking to work it on the legs, a thick outside edge goes down to third man
drives out to mid on and the ball comes back in quickly
oh! Very nearly brilliant! Marsh pops up to a diving Pollard at mid on whose force just can't quite carry him to the overhead snap
stands back and gives himself room to pull, the ball going straighter than he would have imagined, I imagine
on the legs, pulled round through fine leg, just beating the man tidying there and Taylor runs round to oblige
turns ino him, looks to sweep, that shot hasn't brought him a huge amount of success today
an appeal now as yet again he goes for the sweep and misses it
and now he does connect through the sweep but the ball goes up in the air, albeit landing safe of deep square
pushed out and they have to hurry as Sammy comes in with the side-arm shy that goes wide. Australia not afraid to go for the quick singles today
outside off, on the back foot and cuts out to deep extra cover this time
banged in short and Marsh swivels round as he pulls to deep midwicket
some width outside off - and enough for it to be called even though he has suckered Clarke in to cutting at it, Bravo changing his action to not use his front arm at all
pushed forward and they take a quick single
round the wicket, pushed into the covers
opens the face and runs the ball down to third man
some good loop outside off and width, the batsman waits, gets over it and drives out to mid on
outside off, cut right into the ball, sending it the covers
works it to fine leg and there's a very gravelly "Wait on!"
Clarke connects well with the pull, working it out to square
clips to the 45 and they decide not to risk the single
turns it back in towards in from outside leg and the batsman plays at it
driven out to mid on
outside off, cut hard through to deep backward point where Bravo tidies up qickly and powerfully
Clarke's gone! Stepped outside off, tried to run it down to third man and sends a thick outside edge through to Ramdin who takes it two-handed to spark celebrations from Sammy and his team
defends to the covers. He seemed quite surprised by the pace off the pitch there
fired across the left hander who essays a leave and Ramdin takes it around the ankles
pushed across him, driven out to mid off and the sub fielder gets a huge cheer for picking it up quickly (Taylor having an over break)
leading edge first up for Gayle! Hussey looks to turn it away on the on side and gets it incredibly wrong, the leading edge going agonisingly over the bowler's head by a clear distance
defended on the front foot
more defence
driven out forward
pushed out once again
pushed up in line with off, driven out to the covers, a vain cry of "Catch!"
pushed out on the front foot to the covers
forced across him, plenty of width to drive out to the covers
on middle, good length, and defended right back down the track
some width outside off, played down to third man and the batsmen accept the single
on the legs, squares behind it and pushes it straight back down the track
outside off, played down to third man and there's another shy at the stumps from Pollard
on the legs, brushed out to midwicket and they run through the single
some turn back in from outside off and Gayle appeals loudly for the lbw, but he's saved by the big edge back on to the pad
defended on the front foot
on middle and leg now, the batsman thinks about playing with the spin and ends up knocking into the legs
defends into the covers now
more defence right back down the track in line with off
oh, the edge! But goes through the vacant slips area, the hand flying up off the bat as the ball comes across him and he flings his arms at the shot
lets the ball come across the bat and he opens the face to guide it down to third man
pitched up full in line with middle, played back forward
pushed across him again, the batsman opening the face and running it down to third man to rotate the strike
across him again, tighter this time and worked into the covers, Pollard is fast with the retrieval
banged in short and the batsman runs it down to third man and they take the single
on middle, defends right back down the line
pushes to the covers and a quick single is achieved
some width on the legs and the batsman gratefully accepts the chance to pull hard through square
outside off, runs the edge down to third man, the ball going very straight
on the legs, driven out in front of midwicket. Good placement
on the legs, pushed out again to midwicket
guided to gully and can't beat the field
on line, Marsh tries to whip it through mid on but the bowler gets across to stop it
on the pads now and Marsh glances but straight to the man at short fine leg
and there's the breakthrough they wanted! A slightly slower ball in the slot and Marsh drives, can't keep it down and it goes straight to Gayle at cover
on off stump, Haddin defends with a straight bat
defended again, and that's an excellent wicket-maiden from Sammy
nudged away forward of point and that's very good running as they hare through for a single
driven away comfortably to long on and there's an easy single
wide outside off and Hussey cuts square to the man on the boundary
forward in defence on this occasion
on the pads, Hussey can't beat the man at midwicket
tossed up teasingly this time, Hussey goes after it with an uppish drive outside off but it goes wide of cover and out to the sweeper in the deep
driven to mid off and they take off for a very quick single, well run
a touch slower now, on the stumps and Hussey defends
width outside off and Hussey helps it on its way down towards third man
pushed to cover and can't beat Sarwan
slower again, outside off and Haddin nudges to point
dabs outside off again, trying to work it to third man and Sammy groans as the ball beats the bat
angled in to Hussey's pads, he defends
quicker ball, driven to point
cut away to the man at deep cover this time
faster ball, quite a bit of turn in to Haddin, who is cramped up attempting to cut
spins in again, Haddin is well forward and it hits his pad
well bowled, tossed up outside off, there's sharp turn in to Haddin, he misses it, Ramdin misses it and it runs away for some byes
outside off stump, Haddin guides it down to third man
pushed across Hussey, who leaves, and that's a tough wide call, it swung away after it went past the batsman
nudged away towards point and they get through for a run
well, that's quite a shot. Half-volley outside off and Haddin steps forward and simply lifts it over midwicket, one bounce and over the boundary. Seemingly no effort in that shot, but superbly timed
helped on its way down to third man
defended to mid off this time
on the stumps, Hussey clips it down towards long on with soft hands, allowing them to get back for a second
cracking shot from Haddin, Edwards starts with a straight one and Haddin's powerful bottom hand drive flies straight back past Edwards in the air and runs away for four
Haddin opens the face on this one and pushes it behind point
on line to Hussey, he defends
yorker length, outside off and Hussey squeezes it down to mid off, can't beat the field
slower this time, Hussey turns it behind square and thinks about two but Pollard's slide and throw is superb, keeps them to one
shortish ball now, Haddin angles this one down to third man

wide outside off, Haddin tries to cut and gets a thick inside edge a-la Ponting's dismissal, this one bounces into the turf and seemingly wide of the keeper but Ramdin's excellent dive saves some runs
guided away to third man
pushed away to cover and can't find a gap
this time a bit more width for Hussey, who drives forward of cover and out to the man in the deep
well picked up from outside off again. This was a slower one, the offspinner style and Haddin gets down on one knee for a beautifully-timed slog sweep between midwicket and long on
guided away behind point
oh, Haddin tries for another slog sweep but this one skews away off a thickish inside edge behind square leg
down leg side, Hussey tries for a dab sweep and misses
turned through midwicket this time, easy run there
flatter ball from Gayle, on the stumps and Haddin clips it behind square
Hussey goes the reverse sweep, does it well in the end, just a conventional one that runs away for a couple
pushed away towards point again, Hussey not looking for boundaries but turning over the strike nicely
Haddin's feet are rooted to the crease here, he really only half plays at trying to turn to leg and is struck on the pad
turned away behind square leg for a single
no doubt about that wide, tossed up way outside off and Haddin not interested
driven to cover now
a tad short, spins away and Haddin cuts through point
nudged away through cover for a single
punched back to the bowler
good running from Haddin, he pushes to cover and they scramble through
Haddin walks across, Gayle adjusts well and darts one in to leg stump, Haddin scuttles back and gets some pad on it trying to glance
Haddin goes for the slog sweep again, it's wide of deep midwicket though he can cut off the boundary
pushed down to long on for a run
defended towards point, Hussey wants a single but Haddin doesn't
Gayle around the wicket angles it down leg to Hussey, he tries to glance but can't get bat on ball, nor can Ramdin get glove on ball and it's a wide that runs to the boundary
tossed up this time, Hussey tries to turn to leg and gets a leading edge that bobs up safely
faster, on the pads and Haddin flicks a single behind square
round the wicket, pushes it right up there in line with off, forcing the front-foot defence out to the covers
some width outside off, the batsman drives into the covers
down the track and meets the ball outside off with a drive in front of point and the call quickly comes in - "No!"
outside off, opens the face and runs it down to third man
outside off, some width, the ball carries on straight and it's cut out to point
down the track and tees up a strong drive out to long off
a wide, but a relief for Gayle - Haddin missed out on the leg-side full toss
defended this time
more defence
down leg again and the batsman is happy to go down on one knee and pull it hard through fine leg
full toss on the knees in line with off, driven hard to the man at cover this time
doesn't quite get hold of a drive to the covers, instead the outside edge runs down to third man
drags it a touch short and this time he's one knee and pulls hard out to deep square
lots of width outside off, down on one knee and holds the bat out horizontally as he caresses it down to third man
reverse sweep this time
a push forward
turned to the legs, again rotating the strike
comes out and defends on the front foot out towards the covers
a quicker one fizzed past the outside edge as he tried to reverse sweep
forced across him, the batsman waits and meets it at the top of the bounce, he carves it forward and they charge through
dug out on the toes, just in line with off
full toss on the legs, whipped out in front of square. Bravo's a bit unhappy that Benn didn't dive at it as he went to the left
on the legs, turned off down through fine leg. Very full one and it was more of a stab down on it
slower ball outside off, the batsman waits and eases it off down to third man
outside off, driven into the covers on the front foot
on the legs, pushed out on the leg side and his fifty has come up from 50 balls
comes right of the crease to effect the reverse sweep - on both knees - and they turned well, Ramdin taking the throw and throwing on to the stumps but for no reward
defended forward
comes out and drives straight and hard down the ground and he holes out at long off, Pollard took it well inside the rope - stretching up with two hands to pluck it safe
dragged down and pulled round out to deep backward square leg
outside off, plays away from the body and the ball goes on through leaving him a touch
pushed right into the track, the ball skewing out to midwicket
outside off, stretches away from the body to drive out to the covers, it's collected by Fletcher in the deep and he returns well to the keeper
a bit of a false stroke now, reaching outside off to sweep it and the ball carries on over the blade
drags it a touch short once again and it's cut out to extra cover
on off, pushed out to wideish mid on and they shuffle through
short ball on leg, swept up high in the air, but safe
reaches outside off to sweep right round in front of square leg
drives down the ground out to long on
floats one wide down off and the batsman drives out to the covers
some spin right back in from outside off and he works with it, forcing out to square
down on one knee and almosts toys with the fielders as he launches the ball far and in between midwicket and long on, Taylor just couldn't get there
responds with a full one, that is dug out defensively at his toes AKA the yorker
outside off, Hussey comes down the track and drives out to long off where a waiting Pollard jumps, takes and again makes it look easy
on the front foot, pressed out quietly into the leg side
outside leg, brushed fine almost down to the rope where it's quickly returned
dug out in line with off
outside off, drives into the turf, the ball plugs up to the gully
the quicker one and the batsman is quick to stab down in line with off

a huge shout, Sarwan has struck! White tries to lift it from a line with off over midwicket, misses it and goes on to strike him in front of middle, fairly high but not questionably so and the batsman has to go
gets off the mark with a couple after a drive out to the covers
flips this one wide outside off, and the batsman waits as it comes in full and drives into the covers
swings a lazy mow over to deep midwicket on the front knee

gets hold of this one - a good, clean hit from Lee. We've seen him do this before, but that travelled on to the roof of one of the stands, down on one knee and delivers in between midwicket and mid on
pushed out to deep square and long leg runs round
on middle and leg, and pushed out to midwicket
pitched on middle and drummed hard between midwicket and mid on - getting hold of that one very well indeed
steps back, gives himself room, but can only push the ball back to Bravo on the bump - sparking cheers from the crowd which are a touch previous
outside off and this time he drags on a full one back into the sticks, he hears the clicks and has to walk on his way
slower ball, just planted up there on the legs, but it's flicked off to the legs and they run through very well indeed, Gayle a touch ginger in the outfield allowing them the third
attempts the yorker, Lee digs the not-quite-so full one back out to the bowler

inn2.comm: Marshall turns Lee to midwicket and he's off the mark immediately
Gayle leaves outside off
another one left alone
tucked away to fine leg for a single
on the stumps now and Marshall defends
on the pads and turned away to fine leg
pushed across Marshall, he tries to drive through cover and a thick inside edge narrowly misses the off stump and runs away fine for a boundary
down leg side now and swinging further away, he'll bowl that again
pushed towards cover and there's no run
on the pads, turned to square leg and they look like hurrying through for a single but Gayle's not as quick as Marshall with his groin injury and turns him back
left alone outside off
on off stump, defended
defended outside off now
on the stumps and defended
good back-foot drive through cover now, Marsh chases it down well and keeps it to three
good ball, outside off and moving away a touch, Marshall plays and misses
and Lee makes the breakthrough! He digs this one in a touch shorter, Marshall looks to drive off the back foot and the extra bounce does him, a thick edge goes through to Haddin
angled in to the pads of Gayle, he defends
pushed off the back foot to mid off
a bit slower now from Bracken, Gayle pushes it back down the pitch
extra bounce from Bracken, 80.5mph or 129.5kph, driven off the back foot to point
this time Gayle cuts hard, just forward of point and they get back for a couple
probing outside off, makes Gayle play and he defends to mid off
oh, good ball, on off stump and it stays a bit low, Sarwan does well to defend
excellent slower ball, it's the legspinner and draws Sarwan forward trying to drive, it beats the outside edge
Sarwan flashes outside off, this one nips back off the pitch and beats the under-edge of the bat
on the back foot and defending
outside off, Sarwan on the back foot trying to punch through cover but finds the fieldsman
and this one does bounce, Sarwan forced back to defends but it beats the bat

that's pure power from Gayle. Shortish ball on off, Gayle just stands and slaps a pull of sorts, the ball flies over mid off and one bounce over the boundary. Looked a good shot even though it didn't quite go where he intended
pushed away defensively now
Gayle goes again and this is a better shot, slashing hard at a half-volley outside off. It flies over point and again it's one bounce into the boundary
watchfully defended to point
angled in to the pads, Gayle flicks it through midwicket and it's a single
on the stumps, Sarwan defends and can't quite manage to get off the mark

dropped! But that would have a remarkable catch by Marsh. Gayle absolutely thumped that one to cover, it flew low and to Marsh's left, he dived and it was on him so quickly he barely had time to get his hands in position, the ball looked like it bounced off his wrist
turned away to leg
left alone outside off
a miscue from Gayle, he pulls and the ball lobs over Ponting running back at mid on
tip and run from Sarwan as he pushes to cover and gets off the mark

shortish and just outside off, Gayle plays this one pretty sensibly, just getting under it and gently helping it on its way over point. He didn't try to keep it down, but there was nobody in the deep so it was always safe
pushed back defensively to the bowler
turned away to square leg
on the pads and flicked away to midwicket, Gayle turns down the single and Sarwan dives back into his ground at the non-striker's end
pushed away to point
And there goes Gayle. Bracken angles it in, Gayle walks across and tries to work to leg, it strikes him in line, and after a Bucknor-like interminably long wait Asad Rauf raises the finger
on the pads first up and Fletcher defends
and that's three down! Lee was really troubling Sarwan, this one's quick and a bit of extra bounce does for Sarwan, who pushes and edges to slip where Hussey grabs the chance above his head
Bravo clips defensively to midwicket
shortish ball, 90.5mph or 145.6kph, Bravo jumps back and defends outside off
slower one from Lee, it's a bit misdirected though and down leg side so he'll bowl that again
turned away through the leg side
short outside off, Fletcher watches it sail by

that's a good way to get off the mark on debut, Fletcher pushes a confident drive towards mid off, the man dives and knocks it down but the ball still runs away behind the bowler and they're able to pick up three
angled across and defended
pushed across Fletcher, who leaves
good short ball from Johnson, on the body and Fletcher does well to keep it down and get it away to fine leg
angled across outside Bravo's off stump, not quite a wide but not far away
oh, on the body again, Bravo tries to clip it fine, his inside edge onto the hip lobs up behind square leg and just in front of Marsh
Fletcher tries to leave outside off but it's on him a but quicker than expected and it skews off the bat down into the ground and bounces to slip
short outside off, Bravo really wants to hook, shapes to do so but at the last minute pulls the bat out of the way
digs it in again, this time Bravo pulls and doesn't time it, the ball falls a couple of metres short of Watson at wide mid on
short again, the pitch is really quite slow and Bravo has to wait, tries to pull it through the leg side but straight to square leg
good shot, off the back foot and pushed between point and cover, along the ground and well timed
on off stump now, perhaps nipping back a touch and Bravo clips to square leg
on the stumps, Bravo flicks this one away through square leg and there's a man on the boundary who keeps it to one
just outside off, doesn't bounce much and Bravo defends
on the pads and it's nicely worked through midwicket, Marsh does the chasing and pulls it in just inside the boundary
great ball, pitched on off, darting away a touch and Fletcher played and missed
defended back down the pitch
a bit too straight from Johnson, Fletcher is able to tuck it away to midwicket
swing and a miss from Fletcher, he drives at one just outside off and the ball beats the bat
nips back and Bravo pulls in the air wide of midwicket, shouts of 'catch it' from the Australians but it was well wide of the fielder
angled in to the right-hander again, defended to leg
pushed away defensively to cover
pulled away behind square for a single
well played, soft hands as Bravo guides this one down to third man with no slips in
Hopes gets the ball to nip in again, it's pushed away to midwicket
down leg side, not by too much but enough for it to be a wide in one-day cricket
driven hard and in the air, it flies over point and Watson in the deep does the fielding
good probing line just outside off, Fletcher gets a thick edge that goes wide of slips and away for a single to third man
down leg side again, Johnson's radar was off in the Tests and he's bowled better here, but that one wasn't too good

dropped. Oh, Australia's woes in slips continue. Johnson was looking for that edge by pushing it across, Bravo obliged and it flew straight to Hussey at second slip, where he put down a catch that was a little low but quite straightforward

confusion now, Bravo pushes to leg and wants a run, Johnson hares across to field and the batsman turns back, Johnson's throw misses at the striker's end and just as well for Bravo because he was diving and lost control of his bat, he was well out
defended back down the pitch
turned away towards square leg
back of a length forces the defence on the back foot
defends into the covers this time
staright this time and worked to midwicket
on the front foot, waits and defends right down the line
defended on the back foot once more
came back in from outside off, and defends down into it
over the wicket, forced up to the right hander and slightly across him. He defends back in line with off
Bravo decides enough's enough and he steps down the track and drives hard, uppishly, through the covers with a Caribbean flourish of the arms
on the legs but Johnson gets away with it really, the batsman playing off the legs to deep square
on the legs, the batsman punches down his arms on to this one which is wrestled off the pads behind square
on the back foot, pushed slightly across him, he squares behind it and the outside edge skews out to a diving Clarke at backward point who dives to his left and there's a slight misfield
forced into the covers on the front foot, this time he picks it up cleanly and quickly returns
defended on the back foot straight back down the pitch
some width outside off, the batsman crouches and cuts away down through third man
speared on to the pads and pushed back out to the covers
outside off, the ball sits up with some width and it's cut down off the back foot to deep third man
comes across on the front foot, and defends into the covers
defends back down the line
outside off, and a very wide is so signalled
width across the right hander who climbs into a huge flat-batted four, straight through mid off
change of angle, round the wicket and it's pushed forward and they think of sprinting through but Clarke comes in hard and throws at the non-striker's end
pushed forward on the front foot
on the hips, swished very well off the legs through fine leg, Lee does very well to slide round and collect it
nipped back in from outside off, some lift off the track and he defends back down
some width again and Bravo simply leans in and throws his arms at a very easy yet mightily smote cover drive
meanwhile Hopes keeps on bustling, hurrying this one past the outside edge on a good length. He's a tricksy customer all right
defended on the front foot, just outside off
on middle, squeezed down just behind him and they are keen to sneak through the single
outside off, pushed down with an open face to third man
dragged it down a touch and he launches into a well-timed drive lifted over mid off from the base of the bat
on a good length, defended forward now

and he strikes immediately! Bravo takes a long stride forward, misses the ball, and he's caught in front. West Indies are four down now, Bravo could be in some trouble as he stood there for a while shaking his head but there was no problem with the ball itself which would have gone on to hit middle and leg
defended hard on the front foot
quick work from Haddin, appealing for the stumping as Pollard threatented to lift his foot even though it was behind the line. And he looks to have just had his foot down
outside off, some width and the batsman reels off a drive towards the short cover region
defended hard again on the front foot
outside off, defended into the off side
turned in from outside off, pushed on the front foot
outside off, played into the covers
width outside off, drives hard to the covers
oh, half a shout there for one which comes back in from outside off
appeal for pad first, but immediately turned down - plenty of bat evident there
defended on the front foot
clipped off the legs very fine, through fine
pushed right up there in line with off, defended on the front foot
drags it a touch short and immediately the batsman capitalises, down on one knee and lifts it hard over the top between midwicket and mid on
on the front foot, driven to the covers
on the front foot, defended back down the line
outside off, crouched down and opened the face to run the ball down to third man
some width outside off, driven hard to deep extra cover
outside off, cut down to the gully
good length again, driven to the covers
outside off, rocks on to the back foot and drives hard inside out towards the covers - there's a vain cry of "Catch, Punter!" as it goes over Ponting's head
pitches just on leg and Fletcher defends down, sets off, then is casual as you like in trying to get back in and Haddin knocks the stumps at the base and replays show he was well out
outside off, essays the cut once more
loops in on the legs, and it's dug out forward
half-question again, more of a yelp in fact. Either way, it's not being given
pushed down the legs and Haddin whips the bails off more for fun than anything else
finally off the mark with a push into the covers
pushed out on the front foot
goes on with the arm again, and once more it's pushed out forward
some width outside off, cut hrad through to deep point and it's returned well by Watson
width outside off, drives into the covers
some extra loop outside off and "Down!" barks someone sounding like a commando trainer as the fielder at the covers does indeed get down on it
worked to fine leg
full delivery in line with off, boos as the appeal comes in
very good six indeed, Pollard rocks back and drives straight, hard and flat with a great eye
goes inside out on the drive to the covers
speared in full on the legs, defended forward
paddled round to fine leg and Lee thinks he's got the direct hit as they return for a risky second
defended on the front foot
pushed back to the bowler this time
driven out hard to the covers
squares right behind the ball and defends down
some width outside off, cut hard to point
some loop outside off, pushed back down the track
width again outside off and it's cut out to point
outside off, driven out to long off, Ponting with a fumble in the covers
on middle and off, the batsman stands tall and steps into a drive to long on
some float again, patted back down the pitch
and he strikes! Johnson pushes it across him, Pollard edges off the back foot fending away from his body and Haddin snaps up the chance
squared down behind the line, defensively as she goes
some swing in line with off, defended down on the front foot
outside off, driven into the covers
driven to the covers once again and they pick up the single
turned off the legs to fine leg
some width outside off, cut into the covers
wristed into the off side
a big appeal from White as the ball comes right up there - height possibly a factor, although there may have been an inside edge, too
extra loop, driven out to the covers
outside off, drives at it, foisting it to the covers
outside off, pushed to mid on
pushed down to the gully and Clarke shies at the non-striker's end, the fumble allowing the overthrow
some width outside off and throws his shoulders into a flowing drive out to the covers
on the legs, wristed out to short midwicket
outside off, driven hard through mid off on the front foot
driven out to long off
on the legs, turned off behind square leg
shortish ball on off, cut out to deep point
down on one knee, looks to sweep it in front of square
steps back and allows himself to cut hard to point and they come back for the two having been decisive about it from the off
a touch of turn now and on past the stumps as the hapless batsman was down on one knee looking to pull
width outside off, cut out to point and the return throw hits Haddin's left hand
looks to turn it off the legs
some width outside off, cut down to third man
more width and this one is cut away behind point
forced down the channel, not much lift at all, it keeps low and the batsman plays above it
played back down the track in line with off
some width otside off, launches into what would be a powerful drive had he timed it properly - as it is he picks out a fielder at mid off
can only really scrunch a defence this time
some width outside off, cut out to point, trying to force the ball rather than anything
width and room outside off to launch into an inside out lofted drive wide of cover
more width outside off, cut out to point
width outside off, cut through backward point
down the legs, turend round to fine and he slips as he plays the shot and again when he gets to the other end
outside off, chops down an under edge which goes straight to third man, Johnson runs round and tidies up and West Indies take the overthrow
a quick single
this one goes way over his head and the umpire waited to signal the wide
pushed out on the front foot through the covers
width outside off, looks to pull it to square, but it's nothing more than a swing and a miss
width outside off, cut down to point
drags it down a touch short, which is seized on by the batsman who rolls his wrists to move the ball from outside off to square, poor effort from Marsh, a bobble costing them a run
worked out to point
good delivery on off, pushed out on the front foot to the leg side
short ball outside off, swivel-pulled round to square, the bottom hand coming off the bat in the act
banged in short outside off, cut out to the deep where a sweeper is lurking
outside off, a short one, the batsman goes on to his back foot and cuts at it. Lee appeals, he thinks there's a top edge and is upset not to have been given the wicket
banged in short, and swivelled round and out to square
slower ball and Sammy throws his bat at it - quite literally - the blade flaying away out of his hands and he's forced to charge through. A smiling Lee picks it for him and returns it
on the toes, driven out to the covers
outside off, driven hard through the covers on the front foot and he gladly collects the runs
on middle and off, opens the face and runs it down to bring up the fifty partnership
cleans him up now, comprehensively. The ball's a peach, nipping right back in from outside off and the batsman drove right at it, going through the gate
slower ball, driven down the ground to long off
outside off, the inside edge skews to square
short one goes straight over the batsman
short ball on off, swivelled round behind square
pushed at it down through to the keeper, the ball travelled down leg
dug out forward and they think of scrambling a single
outside off, pushed to the covers
down the legs and helped on its way with a reach round, forcing the ball down to fine leg
fired this one through and just to say over the stumps, great ball to end the over
over the wicket, pushed out behind point
slower one, pushed down off, defended it out
forced across him again, and it's played out to backward point
comes wider and round the wicket now, just drags it short and Taylor's not shy of having a big swing - snding the ball between midwicket and mid on; great strike, very clean
slower ball, and the batsman's all mixed up there, looking to play it out to the leg side but his leading edge pops up towards gully, Haddin calls it and carries on over to collect with two hands
outside off, cut hard to deep point and they chase back for two
Lees come in all hostile, trying to finish things off, slamming in the bouncer and he ducks
ouch, takes one on the chest now as he had nowhere to go in defence
some width outside off, the batsman weaves back and opens the face to run it down to third man
defended on the front foot
outside off, pulled round
banged it in short, goes for the pull, takes his eyes right off it but a thick edge flies hard and above Haddin and goes on its merry way
bowled him - although he needed confirmation from the umpire as to whether it came off Haddin's pads or the stumps, both as it happened - Sammy swishing at the air
on the legs, looks to turn it away but it is too late
overpitched and driven hard through mid on, cracking shot
backs away and gives himself plenty of room to drive hard through the covers
and that's it! It's all over, Clarke runs round from long on to take the catch as the batsman attempted to drive right over for the six
